<h3 id="new_reservation">Making a New Reservation</h3>
<ol>
	<li>Click on "New Reservation" or "Start a new Loan"</li>
	<li>Enter in your contact information, and a little information about the event.</li>
	<li>Click Next</li>
	<li>On the next page, you will select what equipment you want. Click on a piece of equipment to the left side of the screen and the description of the item will appear in the middle.</li>
	<li>Press the "Add to loan button" to add the equipment you have selected to your loan.</li>
	<li>When you have filled up your cart with the items that you want, click the "Done" button under the cart.</li>
	<li>You will be shown a confirmation page. Here you will confirm the equipment and the information about the loan before sending it out.</li>
	<li>Once you have confirmed that everything is correct. Click the Submit Button.</li>
	<li>Your request will be sent to CTS. When the loan has been approved you will get an email confirming that your loan has been approved.</li>
</ol>

<h3 id="reservation_history">Viewing Reservation History</h3>
<ol>
	<li>Click "History" in the navigation bar.</li>
	<span class="bold">A list of loans that have been previously completed or cancelled are shown in a table.</span>
	<li>If you want to view the specific information about the loan click on the "View Loan" button in the left column.</li>
</ol>

<h3 id="copying_loan">Copying a Loan</h3>
<ol>
	<li>Click "History" in the navigation bar.</li>
	<span class="bold">A list of loans that have been previously completed or cancelled are shown in a list.</span>
	<li>Click the "Copy Loan" button in the right column.</li>
	<li>This will bring you to the first step of the reservation process.</li>
	<span class="bold note">Note: This will only load the event and contact information, you will still have to select what equipment you want.</span>
</ol>

<h3 id="pending_loans">View Pending Loans</h3>
<ol>
	<li>Click "Home" in the navigation bar.</li>
	<li>Click the "View Pending" button under the second section titled "Pending Equipment Reservations"</li>
	<span class="bold">A list of loans that are pending will be shown in a table.</span>
	<li>Now you can view the loan by clicking the "View Loan" button on the left, or copy the loan by clicking the "Copy Loan" button on the right.</li>
	<span class="bold note">Note: If you decide to copy the loan it will only load the event and contact information, you will still have to select what equipment you want.</span>
</ol>

<h3 id="loan_approval">"My loan should be approved by now"</h3>
<ul class="bullet">
	<span class="bold" >The new reservation system will email you if your reservation has been approved. Before assuming that your loan has been tossed away make sure you have answered the questions:</span>
	<li>Did you give at least 72 hours notice?</li>
	<li>Did I enter in the correct contact information?</li>
	<span class="bold">You can check this by looking at your pending loans and viewing the information on the loan.</span>
	<li>Is it near the end of the semester?</li>
	<span class="bold">Near the end of the semester loan approval can take longer than usual because of the volume of loans. Keep a look out on the home page to make sure there are no announcements.</span>
	<li>If for some reason your reservation is cancelled you will get an email about it. If this happens follow <a href="#cancelled_loan">these steps.</a></li>
</ul>

<h3 id="cancelled_loan">"My loan was cancelled"</h3>
<ul class="bullet">
	<span class="bold" >The new reservation system will email you if your reservation has been cancelled, if this happens to you, follow these steps:</span>
	<li>Check your <a target ="blank" href="{$PHP.BASE_URL}/history/">Reservation History</a> to make sure that the loan is in the list.</li>
	<span class="bold">If the loan is not in the list, simply recreate the reservation</span>
	<li>If you loan is not in the list but you got an email that it was cancelled, email the cts staff at itsmedia@plymouth.edu.</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="new_features">New Features of the CTS Reservation System</h3>
<ul class="bullet">
	<li>While logged in, if you don't finish a loan, you can go back to it at anytime by going to the home page and clicking the "Unfinished Request" link.</li>
	<li>While in the middle of a loan, you can transfer between the different sections of the loan by clicking the green buttons at the top of the page. <span class="bold note">Note: Red buttons indicate you haven't gotten to that part of the process, and white buttons indicate the current progress.</span></li>
</ul>

